Directors of Bush Universal, Inc., and the Hamilton Watch Company agreed yesterday to a plan to consolidate the busi nesses and assets of the two companies.

Bush Universal at present owns about 50 per cent of Hamilton's common shares. The merged corporation will issue 1.58 shares of its common stock for each of the 2,436,000 outstanding shares of Bush Universal and one share of its common stock for each of the 1,406,000 shares of Hamil ton Watch publicly held. Hamil ton is a leading maker of wrist and pocket watches.